SFX, so called after the common homophonic abbreviation "SFX", standing for "special effects", is a British magazine covering the topics of science fiction and fantasy.

SFX magazine is published every four weeks [2] by Future plc[3] and was founded in 1995.[2] The magazine covers topics in the genres of popular science fiction, fantasy and horror, within the media of films,[4] television,[5] videogames, comics and literature.[6] According to the magazine's website, the SF stands for "science fiction", but the X doesn't stand for anything in particular
